{
  "texts": [
    "Users often come across recommendations they have not searched for on Facebook but maybe in another browser or search engine.",
    "They are surprised whenever they see this type of thing on their social media, and it also intensifies their preconceived idea that every social media platform and search engine uses their data.",
    "One of the respondents said, I can understand the product recommendation that I repeatedly look for on Facebook.",
    "But I do not understand how Facebook is able to show me what I am thinking in my mind or what I discussed with my friend.",
    "I am sure, I did not searched it in Facebook, maybe I searched in Google."
  ]
}